snippet.textDisplay:
For those who remember the series Monkey Magic; in my eyes, Tripataka feels like a more reasonable monk than Master Zanzoh in the TV series was. To elaborate; Zanzoh had such a STRONG belief that "all life must be protected" and that "fighting is wrong" that he barely allows Congo (who is the series' version of Sun Wukong) from fighting anyone, even a group of bandits who want to rob and kill them.

Granted, Congo DID often go too far with fighting from time to time. But still; if you're in mortal peril, the last thing you should do is try to make a group of bandits your friends. Zanzoh even tricks Congo into wearing a headband that immobilizes him whenever Zanzoh calls upon its power.

In the original story; while Tripataka IS a devout monk, he's not really restrictive on when and how Monkey chooses to protect him. Plus, he's a bit more playful than Zanzoh
